        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31043",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dordal",
                        "name": "dordal",
                        "displayName": "David O.",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I want to second this request. It would also be great to get some way to get those non-option arguments into the usage summary\n\nRight now, usage in the above example would look like:\n\nUsage: myscript.php [ options ]\n--opt1|o opt1 gets activated\n\nIt would be nice to be able to do:\n\nUsage: myscript.php [ options ] filename\n--opt1|o opt1 gets activated\n\nor at least:\n\nUsage: myscript.php [ options ]\n--opt1|o opt1 gets activated\nfilename  path to the file to work on\n\nThx",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dordal",
                        "name": "dordal",
                        "displayName": "David O.",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-15T12:42:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-15T12:42:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32937",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=megar",
                        "name": "megar",
                        "displayName": "Gilles Bouthenot",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I was looking for this feature is the source. Currently the better way to display the usage message is to extend Zend_Console_Getopt and rewrite the usage message.\n\nI would also request for a way to order these additional arguments:\n\nusage: phpname.php action [ options ]\ninstead of:\nusage: phpname.php [ options ] action\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=megar",
                        "name": "megar",
                        "displayName": "Gilles Bouthenot",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-26T01:22:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-26T01:22:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33508",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=megar",
                        "name": "megar",
                        "displayName": "Gilles Bouthenot",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "One very simple solution would be to split getUsageMessage like that:\n\n<code>\npublic function getUsageMessage()\n{\n        $usage = \"Usage: {$this->_progname} [ options ]\\n\";\n        $usage .= $this->getOptionsMessage()\n}\n\n\/**\n * returns program name\n * @return string\n *\/\npublic function getProgname()\n{\n        return $this->_progname;\n}\n<\/code>\n\nand new method getOptionsMessage, exactly like the current getUsagerMessage() minus the \"usage\" line.\nThis would allow a simple way to display a custom usage message, including actions and additional mandatory argument.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=megar",
                        "name": "megar",
                        "displayName": "Gilles Bouthenot",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-17T00:53:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-17T00:53:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33522",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Remy-\n\nOn its own, Zend_Console_GetOpt doesnt support arguments right?  The only way we've managed to support argument is by adding an option to stop processing:\n\n{code}\n   $getopt = new Zend_Console_GetOpt(..., ..., array('parseAll' => false))\n{code}\n\nThat will force the getopt to stop on non-options.\n\nGilles-\n\nSee above on the argument point.\n\nAlso, I think its worth noting that usage messaging should probably be part of the application itself than the option parsing component.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-17T08:05:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-17T08:05:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
